# Lyx Project Conventions

## Monorepo Structure

- **packages/** — framework packages (`@lyx/types`, `@lyx/sdk`, `@lyx/shell`, `@lyx/cli`, `@lyx/registry`, `@lyx/vite-plugin`)
- **platform/** — admin services (`admin-api`, `admin-ui`, `ssr`, `nginx`)
- **apps/** — user projects created with `lyx init`
- **scripts/** — automation (`platform.sh`, `deploy-aws.sh`, `ensure-infra.sh`)

## CLI is the single source of truth

All MFE operations go through the `lyx` CLI. Never create MFEs manually.

```bash
lyx init <project-name>      # creates apps/<project-name>/
lyx create <mfe> --slot main # creates mfes/<mfe>/ inside the project
lyx deploy                   # builds, versions, uploads MFEs
lyx login -s <url>           # authenticate to a server
```

## MFE Rules

1. Every MFE must `export default` a React component from `src/index.tsx`
2. MFE config lives in `mfe.config.json` (name, slot, version)
3. Versions auto-increment on `lyx deploy` — never set manually
4. Slots: `root`, `header`, `sidebar`, `main`, `footer`
5. MFEs are independent — no direct imports between them
6. Communication via SDK: `emit`/`on` for events, `useSharedState` for shared data

## Code Standards

- Language: TypeScript (strict)
- All user-facing text, comments, docs: **English only**
- No `any` types unless unavoidable — prefer explicit typing
- Functional React components only — no class components
- Use `@lyx/sdk` for inter-MFE communication, never `window` directly
- Error handling: always catch and log, never swallow errors

## Package Manager

- **pnpm** only (workspace-based)
- Run `pnpm install` from the monorepo root after adding dependencies
- Use `pnpm nx run-many -t build` for multi-package builds

## Git

- Branch: `main` is production
- Commits: conventional commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`)
- PR labels: always add `ai` and `cursor`

## Documentation

- `README.md` — user-facing guide, always up-to-date
- `docs/features.md` — complete feature inventory (SDK, CLI, Shell, API, UI, Infra)
- `docs/errors.md` — error knowledge base with cause/fix/prevention
- `docs/architecture.md` — system design, data flow, decision records
- `docs/roles.md` — role-based review framework (Architect, Staff, Dev, QA)

